<p>She went on to explain that when creating perfumes the sisters work independently and don't give input on one another's scents, leaving for a 'surprise' when they each get to see what the others picked. </p>

<p>When the sisters announced the fragrance collaboration earlier this month, Kim explained to fans about the fragrance saying: 'We collectively wanted the diamonds to be a bit more rich, sultry and sensual.' </p>

<p>'Each of the jewel tone colors ruby, emerald &amp; sapphire are unique to each sister and have a symbolic meaning that we really gravitated to and found inspiring.'</p>

<p>Cohesive: The sister's announced their new fragrance collab earlier this month. At the time Kim said:  'We collectively wanted the diamonds to be a bit more rich, sultry and sensual.'</p>

